description: Saw two nights in a row. Heard multiple occasions between 10pm and 3am. Male. Potentially more than one. We recorded his call as he responded to audio recording  of female call. Took photo (bit blurry but lucky to get)

This is just a photo of one of the 15 Kiwis we saw on this walk after listening for their calls at a kiwi monitoring station.
Photographed using a red LED and my phone's night photo mode.  Second photo edited with color removed.

Call is a edited for wind noise and the first few calls of the series were cut out (too much noise).

North Island brown kiwi (Apteryx mantelli) - At Risk/Declining -  Male (first recording) and female (second recording response) calling in the distance at the Brynderywns Hills Complex near Tanekaha Track

Seen and heard on a night walk led by Ness, found on AirBnB - I would recommend this walk!
https://www.airbnb.com/experiences/546229

Two together-a large adult and a much smaller juvenile (photo). The photo is a still from a video using a small red light. I encountered them close to the house on a small track in Kanuka bush. The young one was making this intermittent sound while the adult was silent.  I’d heard one call (male call), and I'm assuming it was the adult. They almost walked into me, and the juvenile seemed to be sniffing me as a stood motionless above him.
